{"aid": "40237654", "title": "HTTP Message Signatures Sandbox", "url": "https://httpsig.org/", "domain": "httpsig.org", "votes": 1, "user": "ajanuary", "posted_at": "2024-05-02 15:53:58", "comments": 0, "source_title": "\u00bb", "source_text": "HTTP Message Signatures Sandbox\n\n# HTTP Message Signatures\n\nThis site allows you to try out HTTP Message Signatures (RFC9421)\ninteractively. This page works in two modes: signing and verifying, both\nworking in four steps. To sign, add an HTTP message to the form, choose which\ncomponents should be signed, choose the signing key and algorithm, and view\nthe signed results. To verify, add a signed HTTP message to the form, choose\nwhich signature to verify, supply the verification key material, and verify\nthe results. You can also find a list of implementations of the specification\nin a variety of languages.\n\n  * Sign\n  * Verify\n  * Libraries\n\n# \u00bb\u00bb\u00bb\n\n# Input\n\nThis service is provided by Bespoke Engineering and Authlete. The source is\navailable on GitHub.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
